	 (N'Crude Death Rate-All Island',N'Death Rate',N'Per 1000 Persons',N'',N'R',N'N',N'A',0,N'Registrar General’s Department',N'For 2010 and 2011 figures are based on place of occurrence.From 2012 onwards,figures are based on usual place of residence.',13,5,N'Death Rate,All Island',1,NULL,'2017-03-01 09:27:46.923',N'STDADMIN','2017-09-25 12:23:29.663',0,1,N'End of August'),
	 (N'GDP - Gross Domestic Product at Current Market Prices (Rs. Mn)',N'',N'Rs.',N'Million',N'R',N'N',N'A',0,N'Department of Census and Statistics',N'The Central Bank began publishing National Accounts estimates in 1959. Estimates for the period 1950 - 1958 have been computed using the growth rates in “Estimates of Sri Lanka’s Gross National Product from 1950 - 1981”, T. Savundranayagam, Staff Studies Vol. 12 No.2 September 1982 and Vol. 13 No.1 and 2 April - September, 1983. Therefore, from 1950-1958 the sum of sectoral shares does not add to 100%. National Accounts data from 2003 onwards based on the estimates of the Department of Census and Statistics (DCS) with base year 2002. From 2010 onwards, data is based on revised base year (2010) GDP estimates of the Department of Census and Statistics. National Accounts estimates were revised in 1970, 1982, and 1996 by the Central Bank and DCS in 2002 and 2010. The GDP and GNI estimates before the revisions are given below. 1970: GDP (current factor cost prices) = Rs.11,705 mn, GNI (current factor cost prices) = Rs.12,671 mn 1982: GDP (current factor cost prices) = Rs. 91,943 mn, GNI (current factor cost prices) = Rs. 89,609 mn 1996: GDP (current factor cost prices) = Rs. 695,934 mn, GNI (current factor cost prices) = Rs. 684,676 mn GDP and GNI estimates of DCS after the 2002 base year revision are given below. 2002: GDP (current market prices)      = Rs.1,636,037 mn, GNI (current market prices) = Rs. 1,611,994 mn GDP and GNI estimates of DCS before the 2010 base year revision are given below. 2010: GDP (current market prices)      = Rs.5,604,104 mn, GNI (current market prices) = Rs. 5,534,327 mn',13,6,N'GDP',1,NULL,'2017-03-13 14:38:16.33',N'STDADMIN','2018-03-21 12:06:20.32',0,157,N'15th day of the third calender month after completion of a year');
